  23:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****   ==============================================================================
  24:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****                         ##### FLASH peripheral features #####
  25:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****   ==============================================================================
  26:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
  27:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****   [..] The Flash memory interface manages CPU AHB I-Code and D-Code accesses
  28:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        to the Flash memory. It implements the erase and program Flash memory operations
  29:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        and the read and write protection mechanisms.
  30:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\bku598\AppData\Local\Temp\ccjOtFBh.s 			page 2


  31:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****   [..] The Flash memory interface accelerates code execution with a system of instruction
  32:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        prefetch and cache lines.
  33:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
  34:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****   [..] The FLASH main features are:
  35:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) Flash memory read operations
  36:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) Flash memory program/erase operations
  37:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) Program and Erase suspension
  38:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) Read / write protections (2 areas per features)
  39:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) CPU2 Security area
  40:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) Option bytes programming
  41:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) Prefetch on CPU1 I-Code and CPU2 S-bus
  42:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) 32 instruction cache lines of 4*64 bits on I-Code for CPU1
  43:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) 8 data cache lines of 4*64 bits on D-Code for CPU1
  44:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) 4 instruction cache lines of 1*64 bits on S-bus for CPU2
  45:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) 4 data cache lines of 1*64 bits on S-Bus for CPU2
  46:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (+) Error code correction (ECC) : Data in flash are 72-bits word
  47:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****           (8 bits added per double word)
  48:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
  49:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  50:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****  ==============================================================================
  51:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****     [..]
  52:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       This driver provides functions and macros to configure and program the FLASH
  53:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       memory of all STM32WBxx devices.
  54:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
  55:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (#) Flash Memory IO Programming functions:
  56:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****            (++) Lock and Unlock the FLASH interface using HAL_FLASH_Unlock() and
  57:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****                 HAL_FLASH_Lock() functions
  58:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****            (++) Program functions: double word and fast program (full row programming)
  59:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****            (++) There are two modes of programming:
  60:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****             (+++) Polling mode using HAL_FLASH_Program() function
  61:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****             (+++) Interrupt mode using HAL_FLASH_Program_IT() function
  62:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
  63:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (#) Interrupts and flags management functions:
  64:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****            (++) Handle FLASH interrupts by calling HAL_FLASH_IRQHandler()
  65:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****            (++) Callback functions are called when the flash operations are finished :
  66:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****                 HAL_FLASH_EndOfOperationCallback() when everything is ok, otherwise
  67:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****                 HAL_FLASH_OperationErrorCallback()
  68:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****            (++) Get error flag status by calling HAL_GetError()
  69:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
  70:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       (#) Option bytes management functions :
  71:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****            (++) Lock and Unlock the option bytes using HAL_FLASH_OB_Unlock() and
  72:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****                 HAL_FLASH_OB_Lock() functions
  73:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****            (++) Launch the reload of the option bytes using HAL_FLASH_OB_Launch() function.
  74:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****                 In this case, a reset is generated
  75:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
  76:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****     [..]
  77:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       In addition to these functions, this driver includes a set of macros allowing
  78:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****       to handle the following operations:
  79:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        (+) Set the latency
  80:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        (+) Enable/Disable the prefetch buffer
  81:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        (+) Enable/Disable the suspend program or erase request
  82:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        (+) Enable/Disable the Instruction cache and the Data cache
  83:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        (+) Reset the Instruction cache and the Data cache
  84:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        (+) Enable/Disable the Flash interrupts
  85:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****        (+) Monitor the Flash flags status
  86:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c **** 
  87:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_flash.c ****  @endverbatim
